channel.title: Auto Cache Help
channel.description: The Auto Cache Downloading bit of my webclient doesn't want to unzip. Or at east I think that is the problem. The client says: "Downloading Cache - x%" and then it says "Loading Cache Library x%" and then it comes up with "Error Loading... Please Report!" But when I go to look in my C:/ drive there is some main_file_cache files and cache version files and a zipped Cache file with everything still inside. How would I go about fixing this code to make it unzip correctly?

item.title: Auto Cache Help
item.dc:creator: @sk8rdude461 sk8rdude461
item.description:
@sk8rdude461 wrote:

It sounds like you’re zipping the cache improperly.
I like to make an empty .zip first and then drag/drop all the cache files onto it.
When you open the zip it should look like what you showed in the second image.
